# Create the dataset for OECD with Standard Errors
oecd_math <- data.frame(
  Year = c(2003, 2006, 2009, 2012, 2015, 2018, 2022),
  Country = rep("OECD", 7),
  Math = c(499, 490, 492, 488, 485, 487, 472),
  Math_SE = c(0.6, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.4, 0.4, 0.4),
  Reading = c(494, 485, 490, 492, 489, 485, 476),
  Reading_SE = c(0.6, 0.6, 0.5, 0.5, 0.4, 0.4, 0.5),
  Science = c(NA, 495, 498, 496, 489, 487, 485),  # Missing Science data for 2003
  Science_SE = c(NA, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.4, 0.4, 0.4)  # Missing Science data for 2003
)

# Create the dataset for Indonesia with Standard Errors
indonesia_math <- data.frame(
  Year = c(2022, 2018, 2015, 2012, 2009, 2006, 2003),
  Country = rep("Indonesia", 7),
  Math = c(366, 379, 386, 375, 371, 391, 360),
  Math_SE = c(2.4, 3.1, 3.1, 4.0, 3.7, 5.6, 3.9),
  Reading = c(359, 371, 397, 396, 402, 393, 382),
  Reading_SE = c(2.9, 2.6, 2.9, 4.2, 3.7, 5.9, 3.4),
  Science = c(383, 396, 403, 382, 383, 393, NA),  # Missing Science data for 2003
  Science_SE = c(2.6, 2.4, 2.6, 3.8, 3.8, 5.7, NA)  # Missing Science data for 2003
)

# Combine both datasets into one
combined_data <- rbind(oecd_math, indonesia_math)

reading<-ggplot(combined_data, aes(x = Year, y = Reading, color = Country)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +  # Add data points
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ poly(x, 3), se = TRUE) +  # 3rd degree polynomial smooth with confidence interval
  labs(x = "Year", y = "Score") +
  theme_minimal() +  # Clean theme
  scale_color_manual(values = c("OECD" = "blue", "Indonesia" = "red")) +  # Blue for OECD, Red for Indonesia
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(300, 550)) +  # Set y-axis limits
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",  # Remove legend
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major gridlines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor gridlines
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14)
  ) +
  # Add text annotations above the plot for Indonesia and OECD
  geom_text(aes(x = 2012, y = 532, label = "Reading"), color = "black", size = 4, family = "serif")

decision_check <- function(cp) {
  dt <- rpart(formula = lowmath ~ . -Math -Read -Science,
              data = train_18_smote,
              method = "class", 
              control = rpart.control(minsplit = 20, 
                                           cp = cp, 
                                           xval = 0),
              parms = list(split = "gini"))
  
  dt_pred <- predict(dt, test_18) %>%
    as.data.frame() %>%
    mutate(lowmath = as.factor(ifelse(Low >= 0.75, "Low", "High"))) %>%
    select(lowmath)
  
  cm <- confusionMatrix(dt_pred$lowmath, test_18$lowmath)
  
  results <- data.frame(cp = cp, 
                        Accuracy = round(cm$overall[1], 3),
                        Sensitivity = round(cm$byClass[1], 3),
                        Specificity = round(cm$byClass[2], 3))
  
  return(results)
}

result <- NULL
for(i in seq(from=0.00, to=0.01, by = 0.0005)) {
  result <- rbind(result, decision_check(cp = i))
}

result <- result[order(result$Accuracy, result$Sensitivity, result$Specificity),]

sch18_global <- read_sas("C:\\Users\\faris\\OneDrive\\Documents\\ECON\\Applied Data\\Final\\SAS_SCH_QQQ2018\\SCH\\cy07_msu_sch_qqq.sas7bdat")

sch18_global <- sch18_global %>%
  mutate(projector_perstd = ifelse(SC002Q01TA != 0, SC004Q06NA / SC002Q01TA, NA))

collapsed_data <- sch18_global %>%
  group_by(CNT) %>%
  summarize(
    projector_perstd_avg = mean(projector_perstd, na.rm = TRUE),
    SC004Q06NA_avg = mean(SC004Q06NA, na.rm = TRUE),
    SC002Q01TA_avg = mean(SC002Q01TA, na.rm = TRUE)
  )

std18_global <- read_sas("C:\\Users\\faris\\OneDrive\\Documents\\ECON\\Applied Data\\Final\\SAS_STU_QQQ2018\\STU\\cy07_msu_stu_qqq.sas7bdat")

std18_global <- std18_global %>%
  mutate(Math = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("PV") & ends_with("MATH")), na.rm = TRUE))

collapsed_std18 <- std18_global %>%
  group_by(CNT) %>%
  summarize(
    Math_avg = mean(Math, na.rm = TRUE),
    ICTRES_avg = mean(ICTRES, na.rm = TRUE)
  )

merged_pisa18_global <- merge(collapsed_std18, collapsed_data, by = "CNT", all = FALSE)

ggplot(merged_pisa18_global, aes(x = projector_perstd_avg, y = Math_avg)) +
  geom_point() +  # Adds points for each observation
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = FALSE) +  # Adds a smoothing line (without confidence interval)
  labs(x = "Projector per Student (Average)", y = "Math Score (Average)",

  geom_text(data = subset(merged_pisa18_global, CNT == "IDN"), aes(x = projector_perstd_avg, y = Math_avg, label = "Indonesia"), color = "red", vjust = -1)  # Add annotation for Indonesia
